<p><a name="Present-day_countries_of_origin" id="Present-day_countries_of_origin"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Illegal_immigration_to_the_United_States&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Present-day countries of origin">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Present-day countries of origin</span></h3>
<p>In March 2006 the <a href="/wiki/Pew_Hispanic_Center" title="Pew Hispanic Center" class="mw-redirect">Pew Hispanic Center</a> (PHC) estimated the illegal population ranged from 11.5 to 12 million individuals<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7" title=""><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup>, a number supported by the US <a href="/wiki/Government_Accountability_Office" title="Government Accountability Office">Government Accountability Office</a> (GAO)<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup>. Of these 12 million, 57% of illegal immigrants originate from Mexico, 24% are from other Latin American countries, 9% originate stem from various parts of Asia, 6% come from Europe and Canada, and 4% from the other parts of the world.<sup id="cite_ref-Estimates_from_PHC_2-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Estimates_from_PHC-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>According to the U.S. Department of Homeland Security<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9" title=""><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup>, the countries of origin for the largest numbers of illegal immigrants are as follows:</p>
